Key Match Events: KL Rahul scored an unbeaten 97* off 115 balls
Rohit Sharma's dismissal led to India losing 2 wickets
Virat Kohli scored 85 off 116 balls but was dismissed
India won by 6 wickets with 52 balls remaining
Post-Match Reflections: KL Rahul expressed pride in the team's performance and win
India maintained their unbeaten record in World Cup matches against Australia
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia elected to bat first after winning the toss
The match was played under a day-night format at MA Chidambaram Stadium, Chepauk, Chennai
India required just 1 wicket to win after scoring 201/4
